<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-01-28T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-01-28T15:00:00-05:00" n="371" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d371">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/5300: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chairman of the American Delegation to the Sixth International
                                Conference of American States</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hughes</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-01-28T15:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January 28,
                                        1928—3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>32. For Mr. Francis White. Text of new draft of proposed electoral law
                            thoroughly satisfactory to Department and to Dodds.</p>
                        <p>It appears that the words “or <hi rend="italic">suplente</hi>” after
                            “political members” and before “if for any reason” in penultimate
                            sentence of Article 2 may have been omitted through oversight.
                            Department does not consider this point important.</p>
                        <p>Above repeated to Managua.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>